         <abstract>
            <p>This paper considers the n-point Gauss-Jacobi approximation of nonsingular integrals of the form ∫&lt;sup&gt;1&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;sub&gt;-1&lt;/sub&gt; μ(t)φ(t)0(t) log(z - t) dt, with Jacobi weight μ and polynomial φ, and derives an estimate for the quadrature error that is asymptotic as n → ∞. The approach follows that previously described by Donaldson and Elliott. A numerical example illustrating the accuracy of the asymptotic estimate is presented. The extension of the theory to similar integrals defined on more general analytic arcs is outlined.</p>
          </abstract>
